cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the problem of disparity estimation in stereo vision. The use of deep convolutional neural networks (CNN) also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The fact that the proposed network is compact and can be trained end-to-end suggests that it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the use of stereo images and the focus on semantic reasoning suggest that it could also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
